Final Project Dashboard

Sidebar

This is my final project for EDLD 652. This dataset comes from Alison Bacon (Link: https://zenodo.org/record/6993478#.Y9xDpuzMKko). These visualizations show the relationship between exposure to adverse childhood experiences (ACEs), trait emotional intelligence (TEI), self-reported health, and socioeconomic status (SES) among a sample of adults. TEI serves as a protective factor against ACEs on self-reported health. However, as exposure to ACEs gets really high, the protective influences of TEI on self-reported health is reduced. Higher SES is also associated with higher TEI. These findings provide more evidence for the need to prevent and reduce exposure to ACEs and increase income equality. Future research might investigate whether interventions that increase emotional intelligence improves self-reported health for individuals exposed to greater numbers of ACEs.
